253
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:00,717
Put it out, Pablo!

254
00:30:09,684 --> 00:30:10,976
Are you with me or what?

255
00:30:13,771 --> 00:30:15,648
And when have I not been with you?

256
00:30:19,694 --> 00:30:22,655
From the beginning,
it has been you and me.

257
00:30:25,533 --> 00:30:28,077
I cannot do this without you.

258
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:34,875
You’re doubting my loyalty, Pablo?

259
00:30:37,754 --> 00:30:39,088
No.

260
00:30:42,174 --> 00:30:45,803
But I’m having serious doubts
with the Ochoas.

261
00:32:18,228 --> 00:32:19,772
Time to thin the herd.

262
00:32:23,192 --> 00:32:24,443
But did we score a goal?

263
00:32:25,361 --> 00:32:27,070
The reporter, right.

264
00:32:29,406 --> 00:32:31,701
Let’s make sure
we score a goal on him as well.

265
00:32:35,037 --> 00:32:35,872
Come on, come on.

266
00:33:00,312 --> 00:33:02,981
You are aware
that I can end your military career?

267
00:33:03,858 --> 00:33:05,609
I don’t give a fuck.

268
00:33:05,693 --> 00:33:08,612
Horacio … don’t give up.

269
00:33:09,488 --> 00:33:13,283
You’ve always been the leader
of the persecution of Pablo Escobar.

270
00:33:13,367 --> 00:33:15,369
Is this how you show your appreciation
for all we’ve done?

271
00:33:15,452 --> 00:33:17,496
This operation
could be a failure before it starts.

272
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,916
I’m not here for fun.

273
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:21,584
What happens is the defence minister

274
00:33:21,667 --> 00:33:25,087
gives you credit for the evidence
that we found at Hacienda Nápoles.

275
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:29,341
So … then if you resign,
I will look really bad.

276
00:33:29,425 --> 00:33:31,427
Is that why you’re doing that?
Is that what you want?

277
00:33:31,510 --> 00:33:35,472
Horacio … you remember when were cadets,

278
00:33:35,556 --> 00:33:38,434
we never thought they would call us
to lead the country’s most important unit.

279
00:33:39,268 --> 00:33:42,354
Horacio, as your friend …
I’m asking you to think about it.

280
00:33:42,438 --> 00:33:44,982
Rodrigo, I don’t even know who Pablo pays.

281
00:33:45,816 --> 00:33:47,359
It could be any of us three.

282
00:33:48,235 --> 00:33:49,445
Horacio, please.

283
00:33:49,528 --> 00:33:52,114
I’ve put my family at risk.

284
00:33:52,197 --> 00:33:55,743
I need the right tools …
if there is going to be a war.

285
00:33:57,077 --> 00:33:58,704
All right.

286
00:33:58,788 --> 00:34:00,038
Perfect.

287
00:34:01,624 --> 00:34:03,166
Then tell me what you need.

288
00:34:05,461 --> 00:34:07,129
Incorruptible men.

289
00:34:32,947 --> 00:34:35,825
Hey, punk. Are you all right?

290
00:34:35,908 --> 00:34:37,994
—Sure.
—Come here.

291
00:35:06,396 --> 00:35:08,231
How are you, son?

292
00:35:09,399 --> 00:35:11,527
How are you?

293
00:35:30,170 --> 00:35:31,839
I have to kill that son of a bitch.

294
00:35:34,341 --> 00:35:38,846
Carrillo’s a cop.
You can always buy a cop with money.

295
00:35:38,929 --> 00:35:40,806
I’ve tried, believe me.

296
00:35:40,890 --> 00:35:42,391
Then offer more.

297
00:35:43,059 --> 00:35:47,938
Or I can loan you Navegante.
He will do whatever I ask.

298
00:35:51,859 --> 00:35:52,943
That’s true.

299
00:35:54,028 --> 00:35:59,324
It’s silver or lead.
That’s the choice for that bastard.

300
00:35:59,408 --> 00:36:04,413
Speaking of lead,
I’m getting a shipment of weapons in.

301
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:06,331
Uzis, grenades …

302
00:36:06,415 --> 00:36:12,337
If I could find a nuclear weapon …
But now I’m negotiating a fucking missile.

303
00:36:12,421 --> 00:36:15,507
—A missile? No fucking way.
—Yes.

304
00:36:15,591 --> 00:36:16,884
Boss.

305
00:36:31,982 --> 00:36:33,483
He’s bullshitting, right?

306
00:36:33,567 --> 00:36:37,863
He’s smoking that shit …
I guarantee it.

307
00:36:40,449 --> 00:36:42,118
Motherfucker.

308
00:36:51,293 --> 00:36:55,131
Mrs Quiroga told me
the neighbours on the block took a vote.

309
00:36:56,090 --> 00:36:57,257
They want us to move.

310
00:36:57,340 --> 00:37:01,804
But we have guards stationed
outside the house 24 hours a day.

311
00:37:01,887 --> 00:37:03,430
That’s what scares them.

312
00:37:06,976 --> 00:37:08,060
Come here.

313
00:37:10,479 --> 00:37:12,397
It won’t always be so, my love.

314
00:37:37,798 --> 00:37:39,466
—Rodrigo.
—Hello, Horacio.

315
00:37:39,549 --> 00:37:41,426
—Everything good?
—May I speak to you?

316
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:43,095
Yes, sure. Come in.

317
00:37:44,888 --> 00:37:46,682
Let’s talk about the incorruptibles.

318
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:49,852
I’m listening.

319
00:37:57,193 --> 00:38:01,238
I’ve been instructed to tell you that
if you cease and desist your operations,

320
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:04,825
you will receive
a one-time payment of six million.

321
00:38:06,035 --> 00:38:08,662
Horacio … that’s US dollars, not pesos.

322
00:38:11,414 --> 00:38:13,083
Instructed by whom?

323
00:38:15,044 --> 00:38:16,962
I think you can guess.

324
00:38:19,173 --> 00:38:20,340
Say the name.

325
00:38:20,423 --> 00:38:22,134
You know who.

326
00:38:23,552 --> 00:38:24,803
Say the name, Rodrigo.

327
00:38:29,558 --> 00:38:30,767
Escobar.

328
00:38:36,481 --> 00:38:38,067
Don’t look at me like that, Horacio.

329
00:38:38,150 --> 00:38:40,485
I’ve always cared for you.

330
00:38:40,569 --> 00:38:44,865
I’m making this suggestion to save
you and your family from terrible grief.

331
00:38:47,701 --> 00:38:49,369
This man has tentacles.

332
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:52,289
I’m surprised
he hasn’t killed you already.

333
00:38:54,208 --> 00:38:55,333
Get out.

334
00:38:57,627 --> 00:38:59,213
Horacio, please--

335
00:39:07,721 --> 00:39:08,847
Horacio …

336
00:39:17,606 --> 00:39:18,857
Take care.

337
00:40:54,203 --> 00:40:56,579
It was about time, Navegante.

338
00:44:46,935 --> 00:44:48,853
Finally, a romantic date.

339
00:44:50,063 --> 00:44:52,107
It’s been a long time
since we’ve been alone.

340
00:44:52,899 --> 00:44:56,653
Just you, me …
and our bodyguard.

341
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:03,952
Like the old days when we were young
and your father watched us.

342
00:45:04,994 --> 00:45:07,623
—My father adored you.
—Yeah, right.

343
00:45:27,559 --> 00:45:28,726
Garcia …

344
00:45:33,982 --> 00:45:36,776
THE EXTRADITABLES

345
00:45:44,534 --> 00:45:46,786
Hello? Yes.

346
00:45:51,249 --> 00:45:52,459
Yes.

347
00:45:55,378 --> 00:45:56,838
But everything is fine?

348
00:45:59,966 --> 00:46:01,176
All right.

349
00:46:17,817 --> 00:46:19,110
Ana?

350
00:46:30,622 --> 00:46:31,665
Ana?

351
00:46:40,965 --> 00:46:42,175
Ana?

352
00:46:46,388 --> 00:46:47,556
Ana!

353
00:46:50,850 --> 00:46:54,479
A little bird … came into the house.

354
00:46:55,104 --> 00:46:56,732
I’m helping it out.

355
00:47:08,034 --> 00:47:09,160
What?

356
00:47:14,457 --> 00:47:16,501
There was an assassination attempt …

357
00:47:18,587 --> 00:47:21,047
on Colonel Carrillo.

358
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:22,424
Did someone die?

359
00:47:24,634 --> 00:47:26,052
One of his men.

360
00:47:29,097 --> 00:47:32,058
It must be terrible,
the position you’re in.

361
00:47:32,809 --> 00:47:36,062
I want you to know …
I think you are very brave.

362
00:47:38,898 --> 00:47:42,652
I’m not brave. Not like Galán.

363
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:45,947
That fear keeps you alive.

364
00:47:47,532 --> 00:47:50,076
That’s what none of them understand.

365
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:57,459
I will support any decision you make.

366
00:51:59,241 --> 00:52:00,409
Hello?

367
00:52:01,661 --> 00:52:03,830
You think you’re hot shit?

368
00:52:03,913 --> 00:52:06,290
You should change your satellite phone.

369
00:52:08,167 --> 00:52:09,585
Who is this?

370
00:52:09,669 --> 00:52:13,255
Your mother’s in Rionegro
with that tub of lard you call your son.

371
00:52:14,382 --> 00:52:17,677
And your wife was at Carrera 11 today,
shopping for clothes.

372
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:19,762
You bastard son of a bitch,
you think that--

373
00:52:19,846 --> 00:52:23,725
What, you think because you’re a cop
I’m afraid of you or something?

374
00:52:23,808 --> 00:52:26,477
You know where my family is, fag,
well, I know where yours is, too.

375
00:52:26,644 --> 00:52:27,770
Don’t forget that.

376
00:52:27,854 --> 00:52:29,146
Gonorrhœa bastard son of a bitch.

377
00:52:29,230 --> 00:52:31,399
Why don’t you take money
like everyone else?

378
00:52:31,482 --> 00:52:34,235
I could have had you living like a king.
But now, guess what?

379
00:52:34,318 --> 00:52:39,741
Time to kill your dad, your mom,
your kids, your entire family,

380
00:52:39,824 --> 00:52:41,910
and you should be smart enough to realize

381
00:52:41,993 --> 00:52:46,622
I have each and every one of them
under watch, you fucking bastard.

382
00:52:46,706 --> 00:52:49,291
Not everyone’s for sale, Pablo.

383
00:52:49,375 --> 00:52:52,128
You just keep hiding and I will find you.

384
00:52:52,211 --> 00:52:53,629
Don’t know when …

385
00:52:53,713 --> 00:52:55,590
but I will find you.

386
00:52:56,382 --> 00:52:58,051
And when I find you …

387
00:52:59,135 --> 00:53:00,970
—I’m going to kill you.
—I’m going to kill you, fag!

388
00:53:01,054 --> 00:53:03,681
I’m going to kill
you and your entire family!

389
00:53:24,869 --> 00:53:26,579
This, then, is war.

